# Library-first: shared primitives live in the library

Other projects use **`@tonyh-2-eightfold/ef-design-system`**. Only what lives in **`src/`** and is exported from **`src/index.ts`** is available to them.

## Rule

**Any reusable UI primitive that the demo or other apps use must be implemented in the library**, not only in the demo.

- **Library** (`src/components/*`): Implement the component, export it from `src/index.ts`, add any new peer dependencies to `package.json` and `vite.config.ts` externals.
- **Demo** (`demo/src/components/ui/*`): For those primitives, **re-export from the library** (e.g. `export { Select, SelectTrigger, ... } from '@tonyh-2-eightfold/ef-design-system'`). Do not implement a separate version in the demo.

## Examples

- **Button, Input, Navbar, Tabs, Select**: Implemented in `src/`, exported, demo re-exports. ✅
- **Select** (after sync): Lives in `src/components/Select/Select.tsx`, demo `select.tsx` only re-exports. ✅
- Adding a new **Dropdown** used by the demo and others: Add `src/components/Dropdown/`, export from `src/index.ts`, add peer deps if needed; in demo, add `dropdown.tsx` that re-exports from the library. ✅
- Implementing a **fancy picker** only in `demo/src/components/ui/` and not exporting it from the library: ❌ Avoid. If it’s reusable, put it in the library first, then re-export in the demo.

## Library styling: Tailwind + design tokens

The library uses **Tailwind** as the foundation. Style components with Tailwind utility classes and design tokens from `src/tokens/` (e.g. `rounded-[var(--radius-8)]`, `bg-[var(--color-button-primary-bg)]`). Use `cn()` and `cva()` for variant composition. Existing components that still use a `.css` file (Button, Input, Navbar, etc.) can stay as-is; new primitives should use Tailwind.

## When adding a new primitive to the library

1. Create `src/components/<Name>/` with `<Name>.tsx` (Tailwind + tokens; add `.css` only if needed for complex or token-heavy styles).
2. Add any new peer dependencies to root `package.json` and to `vite.config.ts` → `build.rollupOptions.external`.
3. Export the public API from `src/index.ts`.
4. In the demo, add or update `demo/src/components/ui/<name>.tsx` to re-export from `@tonyh-2-eightfold/ef-design-system` (and add any new peer deps to `demo/package.json` if needed).
5. Run `npm run build` at repo root to verify.

## Demo catalog: show everything from the library

**Every library component and its variants/sizes must appear in the demo.** When you add or change something in the library (new component, new variant, new size, new prop), add or update the corresponding **Block** in `demo/src/UICatalog.tsx` so users can see it.

- New **component** → add a new `<Block title="…">` with at least one example (and variants/sizes if applicable).
- New **variant** or **size** → add an example in the existing Block (e.g. another row or item) so all options are visible.
- Don’t leave library features undocumented in the catalog; the demo is the reference for what the library offers.

This keeps the library and demo in sync and ensures other projects get the same components from the package.
